Title : Michelle Pye
Text : '''Michelle Pye''' (born 1978) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[association football|soccer]] [[referee (association football)|referee]]. She was given her international badge by [[FIFA]] in 2007.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}} Pye is one of only seven international soccer referees in Canada.<ref name="fifa">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/associations/association=can/footballofficials/referees/peoplekind=wor.html|title=Canada: Referees - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>
She began her career as an official in [[Kamloops]], [[British Columbia]] in the mid 1990s. Since age 13 she has worked her way up to the highest level possible for a soccer match official.<ref name="ksra">{{cite web|url=http://www.ksra.ca/pye_award.html|title=KAMLOOPS SOCCER REFEREES ASSOCIATION (Michelle Pye / Kevin Duliba - Promising Youth Referee Awards)|publisher=ksra.ca|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

== Career ==
Since receiving international status, Pye continues to be a returning official each year.

In 2012, along with Carol Anne Chénard, Dave Gantar, Silviu Petrescu, and Paul Ward, Pye was named again to the 2012 FIFA list of referees.<ref name="canadasoccer">{{cite web|url=http://www.canadasoccer.com/2012-fifa-list-of-referees-and-assistant-referees-p148807|title=2012 FIFA List of Referees and Assistant Referees &#124; Canada Soccer|publisher=canadasoccer.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

Referee Pye was previously appointed to the tournament at New Zealand 2008 and Trinidad and Tobago 2010.<ref name="canadasoccer3">{{cite web|url=http://www.canadasoccer.com/morisset-appointed-to-fifa-u-17-women-s-world-cup-p151984|title=Morisset appointed to FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup &#124; Canada Soccer|publisher=canadasoccer.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

On 27–29 July, [[Ottawa|Ottawa, Ontario]], Canada was the stage of the 2012&nbsp;W-League Championship, the crowning event of the highest level of women’s soccer in the United States and Canada. Three national list officials participated in the event: Michelle Pye, Suzanne Morisset and Sheena Dickson. Pye and Morisset attended this year’s CONCACAF Women’s U-17 Championship in Guatemala. Morisset has also been appointed to the ''FIFA U-17 Women’s World Cup'' Azerbaijan 2012. Dickson was appointed to the CISM World Military Women Football Championship in Germany this past June where was selected to officiate in the Gold Medal match.

Referee ''Pye'' has been on the FIFA List of Referees and Assistant Referees since 2007 while assistant referee ''Morisset'' has been on the FIFA List since 2008. The ''2012 CONCACAF Women's Under-17 Championship'' runs 2–13 May in Ciudad Guatemala, Guatemala. That eight-team tournament will feature Canada, USA, Mexico, Trinidad and Tobago, Jamaica, Bahamas, Panama and host Guatemala. Three of the eight teams will qualify for the FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup Azerbaijan 2012.<ref name="canadasoccer4">{{cite web|url=http://www.canadasoccer.com/pye-morisset-appointed-to-concacaf-w17-p150075|title=Pye, Morisset appointed to CONCACAF w17 &#124; Canada Soccer|publisher=canadasoccer.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>

== Competitions officiated ==

*[[2006&nbsp;W-League]] as a referee for Charlotte Lady Eagles versus Ottawa Fury Women on August 4, 2006.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
*[[2008 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]] as a referee for Germany versus North Korea on November 4, 2008, Brazil versus England on October 30 and North Korea versus England (Semifinals) on November 13. Pye was the 4th official for Paraguay versus USA on November 2.<ref name="fifa4">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/u17womensworldcup/newzealand2008/matches/round=249936/match=300052904/report.html|title=Previous Tournaments - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> Japan versus France.<ref name="fifa5">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/u17womensworldcup/newzealand2008/matches/round=249936/match=300052903/report.html|title=Previous Tournaments - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> She also attended the game between England versus Germany.<ref name="fifa6">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/u17womensworldcup/newzealand2008/matches/round=249938/match=300052918/report.html|title=Previous Tournaments - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>
*[[Football at the 2009 Summer Universiade – Women]] as a referee for South Korea versus Germany on June 30, 2009, Republic of Ireland versus France on July 4 and Germany versus Serbia (Classification round) on July 8.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
*[[2010 Algarve Cup]] as a referee for Germany versus Denmark on February 24, 2010 and China versus Sweden (3rd place game) on March 3.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
*[[2010 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship]] as a referee for Costa Rica versus Cayman Islands on March 10, 2010.
*[[2010&nbsp;W-League (North America)]] as a referee for Pali Blues versus Vancouver Whitecaps Women on July 24, 2010.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
*[[Football at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics – Girls' tournament]] as a referee for Turkey versus Iran on August 12, 2010, Turkey versus Iran on August 24. Pye was the 4th official for Papua New Guinea versus Turkey.<ref name="fifa7">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/womensyoutholympic/matches/round=255437/match=300131876/report.html|title=Girls' Youth Olympic Football Tournament Singapore 2010: Papua New Guinea 0:4 (0:1) Turkey - Report - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> Turkey versus Chile:<ref name="fifa8">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/womensyoutholympic/matches/round=255431/match=300131864/report.html|title=Girls' Youth Olympic Football Tournament Singapore 2010: Turkey 2:3 (2:2) Chile - Report - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref>
*[[2010 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]] On September 12, 2010, Py was a referee for a soccer match of Chile versus Nigeria at Larry Gomes Stadium, Arima held in Trinidad and Tobago from September 5–25, 2010. Also, on September 8, she attended the game between Germany versus South Africa. On September 17, she refereed a match between Republic of Ireland and Japan in the quarterfinals. Then, on September 21, a game between South Korea and. Spain in the semifinals. She was 4th official in the between Germany and Mexico.<ref name="fifa2">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/u17womensworldcup/trinidadandtobago2010/matches/round=253559/match=300125761/report.html|title=FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup Trinidad & Tobago 2010 - Germany 9:0 (5:0) Mexico - Report - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> And 4th official in South Africa versus Korea Republic:<ref name="fifa3">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/u17womensworldcup/trinidadandtobago2010/matches/round=253559/match=300125760/report.html|title=FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup Trinidad & Tobago 2010 - South Africa 1:3 (0:1) Korea Republic - Report - FIFA.com|publisher=fifa.com|accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> and 4th official in Spain versus North Korea DPR:<ref name="fifa3"/>
*[[2012 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship]] as a referee for US versus Mexico on May 7, 2012 in [[Guatemala City]], [[Guatemala]] at Estadio Cementos Progreso.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
*[[2012&nbsp;W-League season]] as a Referee for Pali Blues versus Ottawa Fury Women on July 29, 2012, the championship game. She was one of the officials for the match of Quebec Dynamo ARSQ versus Pali Blues.<ref name="uslsoccer">{{cite web|url=http://wleague.uslsoccer.com/stats/2012/3209865.html |title=United Soccer Leagues (USL) |publisher=wleague.uslsoccer.com |accessdate=2014-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140428020738/http://wleague.uslsoccer.com/stats/2012/3209865.html |archivedate=2014-04-28 |df= }}</ref>
*[[2015 FIFA Women's World Cup]] as the fourth official for France versus England on June 9, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://resources.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/02/63/96/79/eng_11_0609_fra-eng_fulltime_neutral.pdf|title=FIFA Women's World Cup Canada 2015 Match report|publisher=FIFA.com}}</ref> Germany versus Côte d'Ivoire on June 7, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://resources.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/02/62/17/96/eng_03_0607_ger-civ_fulltime.pdf|title=FIFA Women's World Cup Canada 2015 Match report|publisher=FIFA.com}}</ref> France versus Colombia on June 13, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://resources.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/02/64/76/69/eng_23_0613_fra-col_fulltime_neutral.pdf|title=FIFA Women's World Cup Canada 2015 Match report|publisher=FIFA.com}}</ref> and England versus Colombia on June 17, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://resources.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/02/65/06/37/eng_36_0617_eng-col_fulltime.pdf|title=FIFA Women's World Cup Canada 2015 Match report|publisher=FIFA.com}}</ref>

